---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="History + Heritage | Heat & Glo Since 1975" description="Heat & Glo since 1975. The full company history from a single-product Minnesota manufacturer to a leading hearth brand under Hearth & Home Technologies, with 1,400+ authorized dealers across the US and Canada." noIndex={true}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative mb-0 -mx-4 overflow-hidden">
    <img
      src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/96f4f3b6-bb4e-4004-a797-85aa7179b3bb/HNG-True_ForgedArch?io=transform:fill,width:1920,height:680"
      alt="Classic Heat & Glo hearth installation in a stone surround living room"
      class="w-full h-[640px] md:h-[480px] object-cover"
      loading="eager"
    />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-end pb-12 px-8" style="background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(0,0,0,0.80) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,0.45) 55%, rgba(0,0,0,0.10) 100%);">
      <div class="max-w-page mx-auto text-white">
        <p class="uppercase tracking-wide text-sm font-semibold mb-2" style="color: #f97316;">History + Heritage</p>
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold max-w-3xl leading-tight">Engineered in Lake City since 1975.</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg max-w-2xl text-white/90">Fifty years of manufacturing fireplaces in the same Minnesota town. One company's deliberate, uninterrupted effort to get hearth products right.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-page mx-auto px-4 py-12">

    <!-- Direct answer lede -->
    <section class="mb-14 max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-xl text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">Heat & Glo began in 1975 as a small manufacturer in Lake City, Minnesota, building gas fireplaces for real American homes. Today, as part of Hearth & Home Technologies, the brand ships through more than 1,400 authorized dealers across the US and Canada. The manufacturing address has not changed. The commitment to product-led engineering has not changed either.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Timeline with depth -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-10">A five-decade timeline</h2>

      <div class="space-y-12">

        <!-- 1975 -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[140px_1fr] gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="md:text-right">
            <span class="text-4xl font-bold" style="color: #c44a08;">1975</span>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-4 pl-6" style="border-color: #c44a08;">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Founded in Lake City, Minnesota</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">Heat & Glo starts as a focused manufacturer with one goal: build gas fireplaces that work reliably in the homes American families actually live in. Lake City, a small town on the Mississippi River in southeastern Minnesota, becomes the permanent home of the company and its manufacturing operations.</p>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The founding premise is practical rather than aspirational. Gas fireplace technology of the era relied on continuous standing pilot lights that burned fuel around the clock whether the fireplace was in use or not. Heat & Glo engineers begin working on a different approach from the start.</p>
            <img
              src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/94bed5b8-d82a-47db-8823-a5082c371991/HNG_SupremeX_30_Oak_BlkFirescreen_Room?io=transform:fill,width:1200,height:680"
              alt="Heat & Glo SupremeX 30 traditional gas fireplace with oak logs and black firescreen in residential room setting"
              class="w-full rounded-lg object-cover mt-2"
              style="max-height: 300px;"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 1980s -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[140px_1fr] gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="md:text-right">
            <span class="text-4xl font-bold" style="color: #c44a08;">1980s</span>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-4 pl-6" style="border-color: #c44a08;">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">The direct-vent breakthrough</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">Heat & Glo develops and refines its direct-vent system: a sealed firebox that draws combustion air from outside the home and exhausts directly back outside through a co-axial pipe. The result eliminates the need for a traditional chimney while keeping indoor air quality completely unaffected by the combustion process.</p>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">This is not a marginal improvement. It changes where a fireplace can be installed in a home. An interior wall, a basement, a room without any existing chimney structure, all become viable installation locations. Builders and architects begin specifying Heat & Glo in projects that would have been impossible with conventional fireplace technology.</p>
            <img
              src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/6d502d5b-b8b2-4999-8cbe-0794c99b275b/HHT_Birmingham_MasonryBrn_Stacked_HeritageOak_SO?io=transform:fill,width:1200,height:680"
              alt="Heat & Glo Birmingham traditional gas fireplace with masonry brown stacked stone surround and heritage oak logs"
              class="w-full rounded-lg object-cover mt-2"
              style="max-height: 300px;"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 1990s -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[140px_1fr] gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="md:text-right">
            <span class="text-4xl font-bold" style="color: #c44a08;">1990s</span>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-4 pl-6" style="border-color: #c44a08;">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">IPI ignition and the gas efficiency era</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">The Intermittent Pilot Ignition system arrives in the Heat & Glo lineup during this decade. Rather than burning a continuous pilot flame 24 hours a day, IPI generates a spark to ignite the pilot only when the fireplace is called on. When the fireplace shuts off, the pilot extinguishes. The energy savings over the course of a heating season are significant, and component longevity improves because the system is not running continuously.</p>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">This period also sees Heat & Glo's lineup expand across fireplace categories. Gas inserts begin to address the retrofit market, allowing homeowners with existing wood-burning fireplaces to upgrade to gas without full reconstruction.</p>
            <img
              src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/0bf271ce-ef80-4c8c-a7f0-660531aa15bf/Phoenix_StratfordBrick_Angle_Roomshot_180620_2155-Pinto_289-tif?io=transform:fill,width:1200,height:680"
              alt="Heat & Glo Phoenix gas fireplace with Stratford brick surround in angled room shot residential setting"
              class="w-full rounded-lg object-cover mt-2"
              style="max-height: 300px;"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 2001 -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[140px_1fr] gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="md:text-right">
            <span class="text-4xl font-bold" style="color: #c44a08;">2001</span>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-4 pl-6" style="border-color: #c44a08;">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Hearth & Home Technologies forms</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">Heat & Glo becomes part of Hearth & Home Technologies, a consolidation that brings together the leading hearth brands in North America under a single manufacturing and distribution organization. For Heat & Glo, the practical effect is expanded R&D capacity, a broader dealer network, and greater access to the commercial and new-construction segments that were growing rapidly in the US housing market.</p>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Manufacturing remains in Lake City. The HHT structure does not relocate the operation; it extends its reach. The Lake City facility serves as the engineering and production center for Heat & Glo products throughout the HHT era.</p>
            <img
              src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/96f4f3b6-bb4e-4004-a797-85aa7179b3bb/HNG-True_ForgedArchFront_2019Artisan_190613_Lecy_0160-1-tif?io=transform:fill,width:1200,height:680"
              alt="Heat & Glo True gas fireplace with forged arch front in traditional stone hearth setting"
              class="w-full rounded-lg object-cover mt-2"
              style="max-height: 300px;"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 2010s -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[140px_1fr] gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="md:text-right">
            <span class="text-4xl font-bold" style="color: #c44a08;">2010s</span>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-4 pl-6" style="border-color: #c44a08;">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Contemporary design and the linear era</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">Residential design shifts hard toward open floor plans, clean lines, and minimal ornamentation. Heat & Glo responds with a contemporary linear lineup that includes the <a href="/fireplaces/gas/" class="underline" style="color: #c44a08;">Mezzo and Primo II families</a>, thin-frame fireplaces scaled for great-room media walls and floor-to-ceiling stone installations. The category goes from a specialty configuration to a primary specification item on new residential projects.</p>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Cool-glass technology is refined during this period. Engineered air-flow patterns within the firebox manage front-glass surface temperatures actively, keeping them within ranges that meet consumer-safety benchmarks without sacrificing the wide, unobstructed flame view that contemporary linear fireplaces require.</p>
            <img
              src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/d46ab388-275f-4983-b659-7c4cd454dcf5/img-pdp-mezzo-room-shot-05-jpg?io=transform:fill,width:1200,height:680"
              alt="Heat & Glo Mezzo contemporary linear gas fireplace in great room with floor-to-ceiling stone installation"
              class="w-full rounded-lg object-cover mt-2"
              style="max-height: 300px;"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- EPA Phase II + III -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[140px_1fr] gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="md:text-right">
            <span class="text-4xl font-bold" style="color: #c44a08;">2015+</span>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-4 pl-6" style="border-color: #c44a08;">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">EPA Phase II emissions compliance</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">The U.S. Environmental Protection Agency tightens particulate emissions limits for residential wood-heating appliances under the updated Clean Air Act standards. Heat & Glo's <a href="/fireplaces/wood/" class="underline" style="color: #c44a08;">wood-burning fireplace</a> lineup is engineered and tested to meet EPA Phase II emissions benchmarks, with certified efficiency ratings listed on every qualifying model.</p>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">This is not a compliance exercise. It reflects the original design philosophy: a fireplace that burns cleanly is a better product. The combustion engineering required to meet EPA standards also produces more complete burns, more heat output per unit of fuel, and less residue inside the firebox.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Today -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[140px_1fr] gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="md:text-right">
            <span class="text-4xl font-bold" style="color: #c44a08;">Today</span>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-4 pl-6" style="border-color: #c44a08;">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Still manufacturing in Lake City</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">Fifty years in, Heat & Glo manufactures in the same Minnesota town where the company started. The dealer network has grown to more than 1,400 authorized locations across the US and Canada. The product lineup spans <a href="/fireplaces/gas/" class="underline" style="color: #c44a08;">gas</a>, <a href="/fireplaces/wood/" class="underline" style="color: #c44a08;">wood</a>, <a href="/fireplaces/electric/" class="underline" style="color: #c44a08;">electric</a>, <a href="/fireplaces/inserts/" class="underline" style="color: #c44a08;">inserts</a>, and <a href="/fireplaces/outdoor/" class="underline" style="color: #c44a08;">outdoor</a> categories.</p>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">The technologies that define the brand, direct-vent sealed combustion, intermittent pilot ignition, cool-glass management, EPA-certified wood burning, are not marketing claims. They are engineering decisions made one by one over fifty years, accumulated into a product line that works.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Pull quote -->
    <section class="my-16 px-8 py-12 rounded-lg" style="background: #1a1a1a;">
      <blockquote class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
        <p class="text-2xl font-medium leading-relaxed" style="color: #f5f5f5;">"The fireplace is the one room feature that doesn't get replaced. It has to work on the day it ships and on the day the next owners move in twenty years later. That's the standard we engineer to."</p>
        <footer class="mt-6 text-sm uppercase tracking-wide" style="color: #c44a08;">Heat & Glo engineering philosophy</footer>
      </blockquote>
    </section>

    <!-- Product families representing each era -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">The product families that define the lineup</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 max-w-2xl mb-8">Each major era of Heat & Glo's engineering history is visible in a product category. The technologies developed over fifty years are in the fireplaces available today.</p>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <a href="/fireplaces/gas/" class="group block border rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:border-orange-500 hover:shadow-md transition">
          <img src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/937081fe-73df-4957-a0ec-8c5a1bfa3a05/HNG-Primo-II_60-2_2?io=transform:fill,width:600,height:380" alt="Heat & Glo Primo II 60 linear gas fireplace in contemporary living room" class="w-full h-44 object-cover" />
          <div class="p-5">
            <p class="font-semibold group-hover:text-orange-700 transition">Gas Fireplaces</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-1">Direct-vent sealed combustion. IPI ignition. Cool-glass technology. The core Heat & Glo engineering stack, in a full lineup of sizes and configurations.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/fireplaces/inserts/" class="group block border rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:border-orange-500 hover:shadow-md transition">
          <img src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/bfdcf41c-51d9-4ee9-8420-4fc87fe719ca/happy_couple_discus?io=transform:fill,width:600,height:380" alt="Couple reviewing fireplace insert options with a Heat & Glo dealer" class="w-full h-44 object-cover" />
          <div class="p-5">
            <p class="font-semibold group-hover:text-orange-700 transition">Gas Inserts</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-1">For homeowners with an existing wood-burning fireplace. A full gas conversion without reconstruction. Sealed combustion added to an existing opening.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/fireplaces/wood/" class="group block border rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:border-orange-500 hover:shadow-md transition">
          <img src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/96f4f3b6-bb4e-4004-a797-85aa7179b3bb/HNG-True_ForgedArch?io=transform:fill,width:600,height:380" alt="Traditional Heat & Glo wood-burning fireplace in stone hearth" class="w-full h-44 object-cover" />
          <div class="p-5">
            <p class="font-semibold group-hover:text-orange-700 transition">Wood Fireplaces</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-1">EPA Phase II certified combustion. The full-burn fireplace for homeowners who want real wood, engineered to burn as cleanly as current standards require.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/fireplaces/electric/" class="group block border rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:border-orange-500 hover:shadow-md transition">
          <img src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/38e6fc0b-5348-4222-b059-5ec3b95f2b50/img-product-card-si?io=transform:fill,width:600,height:380" alt="SimpliFire electric linear fireplace with LED flames" class="w-full h-44 object-cover" />
          <div class="p-5">
            <p class="font-semibold group-hover:text-orange-700 transition">Electric Fireplaces</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-1">No gas line. No vent. Installs anywhere. LED flame technology built to the same fit-and-finish standards as the gas lineup.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/fireplaces/see-through/" class="group block border rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:border-orange-500 hover:shadow-md transition">
          <img src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/d46ab388-275f-4983-b659-7c4cd454dcf5/img-pdp-mezzo-room-?io=transform:fill,width:600,height:380" alt="Heat & Glo Mezzo linear see-through fireplace installation" class="w-full h-44 object-cover" />
          <div class="p-5">
            <p class="font-semibold group-hover:text-orange-700 transition">See-Through Fireplaces</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-1">One firebox, two rooms. Direct-vent sealed combustion in a partition-wall configuration. Available in linear and traditional geometries.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/fireplaces/outdoor/" class="group block border rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:border-orange-500 hover:shadow-md transition">
          <img src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/c220ce20-e963-4c07-85ca-83fa16359ef4/Nest-Out-West-Basem?io=transform:fill,width:600,height:380" alt="Outdoor fireplace installation from Heat & Glo" class="w-full h-44 object-cover" />
          <div class="p-5">
            <p class="font-semibold group-hover:text-orange-700 transition">Outdoor Fireplaces</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-1">Built for outdoor installation. Weather-resistant construction. The same sealed combustion system applied to patios, outdoor rooms, and covered porches.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA band 1 -->
    <section class="rounded-lg p-8 mb-12" style="background: #c44a08;">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Find an authorized dealer near you</h2>
          <p class="text-white/85 mt-1">More than 1,400 authorized locations across the US and Canada. Your local dealer carries current product, handles installation, and knows the lineup.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="/where-to-buy/" style="background: #fff; color: #c44a08; padding: 0.75rem 1.75rem; border-radius: 0.375rem; font-weight: 700; white-space: nowrap; text-decoration: none; display: inline-block;">Find a Dealer</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Manufacturing and quality section -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Why manufacturing in Lake City still matters</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The decision to keep manufacturing in Lake City, Minnesota, rather than offshore it for lower unit costs, is one of the more consequential decisions in Heat & Glo's history. It means the engineering teams and the manufacturing floor are in the same place. Problems found in testing get corrected at the source. Product changes move from design to production without a supply chain that introduces delay and variability.</p>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">It also means the company can maintain the kind of quality control that matters for a product with a twenty-plus-year useful life. Fireplaces are not consumer electronics. They do not get replaced every three years. The one installed today is the one a homeowner's children inherit. Manufacturing standards have to reflect that.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">What the 1,400+ dealer network represents</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Heat & Glo products are sold through authorized dealers rather than through big-box retail for a deliberate reason. The complexity of a fireplace installation, gas line sizing, vent routing, clearance-to-combustibles requirements, local building codes, surround material selection, does not belong in a transaction where the customer is on their own after checkout.</p>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">An authorized dealer knows the product technically. They have completed the training that HHT requires. They can size the unit to the room, confirm the vent path, and ensure the installation meets every applicable standard. The sale and the expertise come together.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Inline image break -->
    <section class="mb-16 -mx-4">
      <img src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/487a4332-ec09-4301-bb0b-d13b860a682d/HNG_Get-Inspired_Ga?io=transform:fill,width:1920,height:520" alt="Heat & Glo fireplace inspiration gallery collage" class="w-full h-[320px] object-cover rounded-none" />
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ section -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Common questions about Heat & Glo's history</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 max-w-3xl">
        <details class="border rounded-lg">
          <summary class="px-5 py-4 font-semibold cursor-pointer hover:bg-neutral-50">Where are Heat & Glo fireplaces manufactured?</summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-4 text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">Lake City, Minnesota. The company has manufactured in the same location since it was founded in 1975. Manufacturing has not moved offshore. The production facility and the engineering team are in the same place.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="border rounded-lg">
          <summary class="px-5 py-4 font-semibold cursor-pointer hover:bg-neutral-50">Is Heat & Glo still an independent company?</summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-4 text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">Heat & Glo is a brand within Hearth & Home Technologies, which formed in 2001. HHT is the largest hearth products manufacturer in North America. Heat & Glo operates as a distinct brand within that structure, with its own product lineup, dealer network, and manufacturing operations.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="border rounded-lg">
          <summary class="px-5 py-4 font-semibold cursor-pointer hover:bg-neutral-50">How many dealers carry Heat & Glo?</summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-4 text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">More than 1,400 authorized dealers across the US and Canada. These are specialty hearth retailers and full-service fireplace dealers who have completed HHT's dealer training and carry current Heat & Glo product. You can locate the nearest authorized dealer using the dealer finder.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="border rounded-lg">
          <summary class="px-5 py-4 font-semibold cursor-pointer hover:bg-neutral-50">What is the ProAdvantage program?</summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-4 text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">ProAdvantage is Heat & Glo's trade program for builders, architects, interior designers, and mechanical contractors. Members get access to CAD files, spec sheets, continuing education credits, and a dedicated trade support line. If you are specifying Heat & Glo products for a project, registering for ProAdvantage is worth doing before the project reaches rough-in.</div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA band 2 -->
    <section class="border rounded-lg p-8 mb-12">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">Specifying for a project? Join ProAdvantage.</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mt-1">CAD files, spec sheets, trade pricing, and a dedicated help desk for builders, architects, and design professionals.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="/pro/" style="background: #c44a08; color: #fff; padding: 0.75rem 1.75rem; border-radius: 0.375rem; font-weight: 700; white-space: nowrap; text-decoration: none; display: inline-block;">ProAdvantage</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
      Related: <a href="/key-technologies/" class="underline">Key Technologies</a> &middot; <a href="/about-us/" class="underline">About Heat & Glo</a> &middot; <a href="/about-us/epa-certification/" class="underline">EPA Certification</a>
    </p>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>
